a481_913x149.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg" width="913" height="149" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:149,&quot;width&quot;:913,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:28873,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2d9b33d2-b0b7-4389-8725-9cd95359a481_913x149.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></figure></div><p>这种态度的旧称是<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irredentism">民族统一主义</a>。</p><p>这个“解决方案”根本不是解决方案，而是大规模暴行——驱逐或屠杀数百万人。一些西方左派认为这一结果代表了正义，这是对西方左派的严厉控诉。而且，这种结果将公然违反国家主权原则；以色列得到国际承认，接受它从地图上消失将是对全球秩序的巨大打击。</p><p>无论如何，以色列人本身并不认为自己是恰好生活在中东的临时居民；他们认为自己是中东地区的临时居民。他们出生在以色列，这是他们的祖国，他们将竭尽全力反对大规模驱逐或灭绝，使用他们可以使用的所有武器（包括核武器）。美国等国家将支持这场斗争。</p><p>因此，对以色列进行种族清洗以建立一个单一的巴勒斯坦国，无论从道义上还是实际上都是不可能的。同样，以色列对约旦河西岸和加沙地带的巴勒斯坦人进行种族清洗的想法既不合理，也极不可能发生。</p><p>让我们继续讨论另一个“单一国家解决方案”。以色列-巴勒斯坦多民族国家的想法受到西方一些自由主义者的青睐。先例就是以色列本身，尽管存在普遍的种族歧视、不平等以及以色列作为一个“犹太国家”的正式身份，但犹太人和阿拉伯人作为一个民族和平地生活在一起。按照这种观点，约旦河西岸和（也许）加沙实际上已经是以色列国家的一部分，看似民族分离的东西实际上只是一个种族隔离政权。根据这种观点，实施一国解决方案所需要做的就是以色列结束其种族隔离政策，并给予巴勒斯坦人作为其所属国家公民的充分权利。</p><p>这是完全行不通的，因为双方都不希望这样。巴勒斯坦人不希望这样，正如上面的民意调查所证明的那样，民意调查显示，大多数人支持民族统一主义和种族清洗，而对拥有平等权利的共同民主国家的支持程度较低。以色列人不希望这样，因为他们知道这将导致他们企图进行种族清洗和/或种族灭绝，这将导致双方的血腥内战、重新分裂和种族清洗，类似于在1948年。</p><p>一个简单的事实是，以色列人和巴勒斯坦人已经互相争斗太久了，不可能很快成为一个共同国家的公民。我们可以希望情况并非如此，但希望不会实现。因此，任何形式的“一国解决方案”都是完全不可能的。无论西方左派、伊朗或社交媒体上的各种流氓如何怂恿巴勒斯坦民族统一主义者，这都不会发生。</p><h4>为什么两国解决方案行不通</h4><p>《奥斯陆协议》中规定的两国解决方案是行不通的，因为加沙和约旦河西岸不会成为一个国家的一部分。首先，也是最重要的是，它们是不连续的。不毗邻国家的历史记录非常糟糕，<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh_genocide">巴基斯坦和孟加拉国</a>的命运就证明了这一点。当然，阿拉斯加是个例外，但阿拉斯加大部分都是空旷的荒野；我怀疑如果阿拉斯加人口变得更多，它会试图脱离。相比之下，加沙和约旦河西岸的人口大致相当，约为 200 万至 300 万。</p><p>考虑交通。与阿拉斯加或加里宁格勒甚至孟加拉国不同，西岸是内陆地区。加沙人和约旦河西岸的巴勒斯坦人要访问彼此的领土，就必须沿着一条以色列可以随时选择关闭的陆地走廊穿越以色列；这将彻底损害巴勒斯坦主权。巴勒斯坦国将受到以色列的摆布，因为以色列总是可以威胁将其一分为二。</p><p>更重要的是，政治控制是通过面对面的关系、社会服务、基础设施建设等在当地建立的。这意味着加沙和西岸自然会倾向于由两个不同的政治领导人控制。事实上，这正是已经发生的事情。哈马斯和法塔赫这两个拥有武装民兵的巴勒斯坦政党<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatah%E2%80%93Hamas_conflict">曾于 2007 年相互交战</a>；前者盛行于加沙，后者盛行于西岸。</p><p>这意味着加沙和西岸只是一个“国家”的一部分，因为他们都认为自己是巴勒斯坦人，他们都梦想有一个统一的巴勒斯坦国，并且国际社会认为他们是一个民族的一部分。但在地理、经济、政治和军事上，它们已经是独立的实体。由于以色列不太可能从地图上消失，因此在任何可预见的“解决方案”中，它们都将仍然是独立的实体。</p><p>因此，两国解决方案实际上是不可能的，而且一直都是不可能的——不是因为以色列的行动或巴勒斯坦民族统一主义，而是因为加沙和西岸实际上不可能保持团结。</p><h4>三态解决方案会是什么样子</h4><p>三国解决方案就是我们可以笼统地称为“威斯特伐利亚”解决方案——将所有可用土地和人口划分为国际公认的民族国家，并具有充分的地方自决权。简而言之，每个人都可以继续生活在自己居住的地方，每个人都可以拥有自己的国家。</p><p>当然，我不是第一个提出这个想法的人——它太明显了。您可以阅读<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070621194402/http://atimes.com/atimes/Middle_East/IF20Ak04.html">Kaveh Afrasiabi</a> 、 <a href="https://www.tabletmag.com/sections/israel-middle-east/articles/three-state-solution-benjamin-kerstein-peace-israel-palestine">Benjamin Kerstein</a> 、 <a href="https://www.latimes.com/la-oe-savage20jun20-story.html">Jacob Savage</a>等人撰写的有关它的文章。但这个想法并没有得到应有的关注或支持。</p><p>三国解决方案需要国际社会承认加沙和西岸为独立国家，并享受由此带来的所有好处。<a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2021/3/14/a-guide-to-the-gaza-strip">以色列对加沙边界、水域和领空的控制</a>将被视为战争行为而不是占领——不是“种族隔离”，而是类似于任何其他军事封锁的封锁。如果加沙和以色列互相轰炸或袭击，这些将被视为边境战争，而不是警察行动或恐怖主义。</p><p>这场战争可能会持续很长时间，但可能不会永远持续下去。几十年来，事实证明，民族国家体系非常擅长通过国际压力和相互军事疲惫的结合来结束边境战争。正如乌克兰所展示的那样，军事技术正在转向防御，这一事实也意味着以色列和加沙最终都会有停止战斗的动机。</p><p>经济学将是另一个强大的激励因素。目前，由于海上贸易被切断，加沙无法积累财富。其人均 GDP <a href="https://thedocs.worldbank.org/en/doc/65cf93926fdb3ea23b72f277fc249a72-0500042021/related/mpo-pse.pdf">估计仅为 1257 美元</a>，使其成为地球上最贫困的地方之一。如果黎巴嫩独立并能够进行海上贸易，这个数字无疑会猛增——黎巴嫩的人均GDP大约是这个数字的3倍。最容易发展的行业就是旅游业——加沙有很多美丽的海滩、大量的历史古迹等。未来它将成为土耳其、可能还有海湾国家和欧洲的投资目的地。</p><p>所有这一切都需要独立的加沙与以色列签署持久停战协议。这将给哈马斯领导层带来压力，要求其接受在一些巴勒斯坦人看来是令人羞辱的妥协方案。这<em>不会</em>迫使他们结束民族统一主义言论；他们可以而且会继续谈论“从河流到海洋”的巴勒斯坦，并宣布他们打算有一天摧毁以色列。但有一天不是今天。</p><p>出于两个原因，西岸向独立民族国家过渡将面临更加困难的时期。首先，它地处内陆，与海上贸易隔绝，经济发展受到一定影响。但更重要的是，由于以色列在过去几十年里对非法定居者运动的支持，约旦河西岸拥有约<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli_settlement">45 万以色列定居者</a>。这意味着，如果西岸要成为一个独立国家，这些定居者将必须要么 A）作为该国家内的宗教少数群体生活，要么 B）搬迁。</p><p>显然，这些选择中的任何一个都会违反我上面概述的三个原则之一。巴勒斯坦人不太可能以平等的权利对待本国的犹太定居者，并且可能会出现部族间暴力和最终的内战，以色列支持定居者，哈马斯和伊朗支持巴勒斯坦人，双方都会发生暴行和种族清洗。另一方面，以色列定居者被迫离开定居点是种族清洗。因此，无论定居者发生什么，都将是一件坏事。以色列政府鼓励定居者运动的殖民主义行为注定不会有幸福的结局。现在的目标应该是以尽量减少悲剧的方式结束它。</p><p>悲剧性最小的解决方案可能是让大多数定居者迁移到以色列边境附近一些地理上较小的定居点，然后以色列吞并这些地区。这是一张地图，表明这是相当可行的： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg" width="640" height="1277.8021978021977" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:2907,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:640,&quot;bytes&quot;:1189833,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F271b7a83-799a-44d1-89e0-0a4c2b352eae_1920x3834.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-52756427">英国广播公司</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这个解决方案会让很多人非常生气，因为它将巩固以色列的一些征服——重要的是包括东耶路撒冷。巴勒斯坦人不会容忍这一点——但是，正如民意调查显示，他们根本不容忍以色列的存在，所以那里不会有太大改变。与加沙问题一样，三国解决方案并不意味着巴勒斯坦方面民族统一主义言论的终结。</p><p>至于国际社会，他们可以承认约旦河西岸巴勒斯坦国的独立<em>，但不</em>承认以色列的领土征服。我们这样做的例子已经很多了——例如，我们承认俄罗斯和乌克兰，但我们不承认克里米亚是俄罗斯的一部分。因此，西岸定居点将成为一场“冻结冲突”，就像东欧和高加索地区的许多定居点一样。但“冻结”部分确实是关键——承认西岸是一个独立的民族国家，并与以色列停战，西岸将能够和平发展并享有安全。一些领土将会丢失，仇恨和民族统一主义不会消失，但“种族隔离”政权将完全消失。以色列将不再陷入永恒的占领，使其能够在更稳定的边界内更安全、更和平地发展。</p><p>这就是三态解决方案。这显然并不完美，并且会涉及大量的痛苦和愤怒，以及一些持续的暴力。但是，主权的、国际公认的、独立的民族国家的“威斯特伐利亚”体系是迄今为止为组织人民之间土地分配而设计的最佳体系，没有理由认为这不是以色列人和巴勒斯坦人的最佳选择以及。</p><p>换句话说，（几乎）每个人都应该继续生活在他们现在居住的地方，并拥有一个国家。</p><p>当然，更困难的问题是如何从这里到达那里。加沙和约旦河西岸的巴勒斯坦人不太可能简单地宣布他们目前控制的领土独立。以色列必须单方面撤军和定居者，并宣布约旦河西岸和加沙地带独立。这将使加沙人和约旦河西岸的巴勒斯坦人做出选择：要么正式承认并获得所有相关的经济和安全利益，要么避免承认以表明对民族统一主义的承诺。我敢打赌，他们会选择前者，尽管可能需要一段时间才能改变。无论如何，考虑到短期安全风险和以色列右翼对定居者运动的意识形态承诺，尚不清楚以色列如何有动力做这样的事情。</p><p>但在我看来，像这样的三国解决方案<em>必须</em>成为以色列/巴勒斯坦的长期结局，其他所有解决方案似乎都不太可行。如果你有更好的想法，不涉及大规模种族清洗或关于以色列人和巴勒斯坦人作为一个民族联合起来的不切实际的假设，我很想听听。</p><p><em>注意：这篇文章的原始版本没有考虑以色列将巴勒斯坦人驱逐出约旦河西岸和加沙的选择。不用说，这不是一个可行的“一国解决方案”。</em> </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/a-three-state-solution-is-the-only?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/a-three-state-solution-is-the-only?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
You're not going to like what comes after Pax AmericanaWelcome to the jungle. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/youre-not-going-to-like-what-c​​omes https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/youre-not-going-to-like-what-c​​omesNoah Smith Sat, 07 Oct 2023 20:04:38 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg" width="1123" height="751" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:751,&quot;width&quot;:1123,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:315399,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe5cb9f9c-05bf-46c1-97a7-71c0631ddebf_1123x751.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p> <em>“我可能是对的，也可能是错的/但当我离开时你会想念我的”——泰姬陵</em></p><p>昨天，正如您可能听说的那样，哈马斯<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/10/07/israel-gaza-timeline-videos-maps/">对以色列发动了大规模突然袭击</a>，从加沙越过边境，在大规模火箭弹袭击后占领或袭击了附近的城镇，<a href="https://twitter.com/jacobhelberg/status/1710735884059070748">造成数百人死亡</a>。哈马斯士兵将以色列俘虏带入加沙的<a href="https://time.com/6321586/israel-hamas-attack-gaza-strip-deaths/">场景</a>在互联网上大量传播。作为回应，以色列宣布进入战争状态，双方之间的战斗有望比近期记忆中的任何战斗都更具破坏性和恶毒。</p><p>正如许多人已经<a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/iran-hamas-attacks-against-israel-palestine-jerusalem/">指出的</a>那样，这次袭击可能是为了破坏美国一直<a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/us-talks-saudi-arabia-israel-normalization-deal-rcna116464">试图促成的</a>以色列与沙特达成和平协议的可能性。这样的协议——这将是特朗普发起的“亚伯拉罕协议”进程的延续——将使哈马斯更难从沙特的捐助者那里获得资金；这也意味着每个主要的逊尼派阿拉伯国家都承认以色列国，这意味着哈马斯作为什叶派伊朗客户以外的形象将被打破。</p><p>如果哈马斯成功破坏以色列与沙特的协议，这将打击美国的威望以及美国自称具有稳定、缔造和平影响力的形象。但即使以色列与沙特的协议最终达成，这次袭击也表明美国遏制世界各地冲突的能力正在下降。</p><p>这也不是最近爆发的唯一一次州际冲突。最近几周，阿塞拜疆全面收回纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫领土，导致 12 万亚美尼亚人逃亡——这是一场大规模的<a href="https://www.cfr.org/article/ethnic-cleansing-happening-nagorno-karabakh-how-can-world-respond">种族清洗</a>。其主要原因是俄罗斯专注于入侵乌克兰。阿塞拜疆在 2020 年的战争中击败了亚美尼亚，并正式控制了纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫，但俄罗斯介入并阻止了进一步的暴力事件。随着俄罗斯实力的衰落，亚美尼亚试图<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/armenia-us-military-exercise-kicks-off-near-yerevan-us-spokesperson-2023-09-11/">迅速转向美国</a>，但这不足以阻止阿塞拜疆的种族清洗。</p><p>与此同时，塞尔维亚正在与科索沃接壤的边境<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/10/05/serbia-and-kosovo-could-easily-slip-into-war-analysts-warn.html">增兵</a>，自20世纪90年代美国干预塞尔维亚以来，科索沃的独立一直存在争议。美国及其一些盟国<a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/2/17/mapping-the-countries-that-recognise-kosovo-as-a-state-2">承认科索沃</a>独立于塞尔维亚，但塞尔维亚、俄罗斯、中国和其他一些欧洲国家并不承认。</p><p>这些只是全球秩序瓦解的几个迹象。<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pax_Americana">美国治下的和平</a>即使还没有完全消亡，也已经处于严重的衰败状态。一个全面多极化的世界已经出现，人们也姗姗来迟地认识到，多极化是相当混乱的。</p><p>什么是美国治下的和平？冷战结束后，国家间冲突（国家之间的战争、帝国征服以及国家干预内战）造成的死亡人数急剧下降。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png" width="1020" height="720" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:720,&quot;width&quot;:1020,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:108124,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2cc495e1-b115-4794-86ad-cf5b39136023_1020x720.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/death-rate-in-state-based-conflicts-by-conflict-type">OWID</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>没有外国实质性干预的内战<a href="https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/ongoing-state-based-conflicts-by-type">很常见</a>，但除了中国或俄罗斯偶尔发生的怪物内战外，它们往往不会造成很多人死亡； it&#39;s when countries send their armies to fight beyond their borders that the big waves of destruction usually happen. And for almost 70 years after the end of World War 2, this happened less and less. Historians call this <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Peace">the Long Peace</a> . The lowest level of interstate conflict came from 1989 through 2011, after the collapse of the USSR, when the US became the world&#39;s sole superpower.</p><p> Political scientists and historians have many theories for why the Long Peace happened (and there are even a few who think it was just a statistical illusion). Democratic peace theory says that countries fought less because their people brought their leaders under tighter control. Capitalist peace theory says that the spread of global trade and financial links made war less attractive economically; it&#39;s also possible that rich countries are more materially satisfied and thus less likely to fight. The UN and other international organizations may have also tamped down conflict.</p><p> But the simplest and most parsimonious explanation for the Long Peace is that American power kept the peace. If countries sent their armies into other countries, there was always the looming possibility that America and its allies could intervene to stop them — as they did in the Korean War in 1950, the Gulf War of 1991, Bosnia in 1992 in Bosnia, Kosovo in 1999, and so on. Soviet power occasionally helped as well, as when the USSR helped India intervene to end the Bangladeshi genocide in 1971. But overall the Soviet Union was a revisionist power that was <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_interventions_by_the_Soviet_Union">more likely to start wars</a> than end them, while the US and its allies, being the most powerful bloc, preferred to keep the status quo.</p><p> Of course, it&#39;s difficult to draw the line between interventions that prevent conflict and interventions that stir it up. Was the Vietnam War a US attempt to halt a North Vietnamese takeover of South Vietnam, or was it the US intervening in an internal South Vietnamese civil war? The answer depends on your point of view. But note that even the possibility of an intervention that ultimately makes a conflict worse <em>can still serve as a deterrent</em> . If there&#39;s a crazy guy who will go anywhere there&#39;s a fight and start shooting bullets into the crowd, that&#39;s a good reason to avoid starting a fight.</p><p> In fact, the outbreak of interstate conflict in the late 60s and early 70s fits the Pax Americana theory quite well. The US was absorbed with the war in Vietnam during those years, and thus had far fewer resources and attention available to intervene in other conflicts. When the cat is away, the mice will play, as they say.</p><p> The US thus functioned as a global policeman. The movie <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Team_America:_World_Police">Team America: World Police</a> made fun of this idea, but also <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=32iCWzpDpKs">kind of supported it</a> . As long as the US and its alliances were sitting there waiting to throw their weight into any interstate conflict, there was inherent risk involved in any sort of extraterritorial intervention.</p><p> Or so the theory goes, anyway. It&#39;s not easily possible to test the Pax Americana hypothesis empirically, for the same reason that it&#39;s hard to know what causes recessions. American power affected the whole globe, so it&#39;s hard to do a cross-country analysis. And there aren&#39;t that many interstate wars, so data is sparse. Your best bet would probably be to construct some sort of measure of how susceptible a country was to the risk of US intervention — some quantitative definition of a US “sphere of influence” — and then to look at how shocks to America&#39;s intervention capability, like the Vietnam War, differentially affected countries that were more or less subject to US intervention. But the data set would be very small, and there would be a lot to control for, and so I&#39;m not sure how much I&#39;d trust this empirical exercise.</p><p> Pax Americana died in stages over the last two decades; <a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2012/04/the-end-of-pax-americana-how-western-decline-became-inevitable/256388/">people</a> have been <a href="https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/japan/2022-06-13/real-end-pax-americana">writing</a> about its <a href="https://www.chathamhouse.org/sites/default/files/images/ia/INTA94_1_6_249_Layne.pdf">death</a> for a <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/opinions/2006/12/14/farewell-to-pax-americana/a2445f16-fb7b-4c63-be07-6deca0704aa7/">while now</a> , and there were a number of factors that killed it. First there was the Iraq War, which was a clear-cut case of the US starting a major international conflict rather than interceding to stop one. Saddam Hussein was brutal, but after his 1991 defeat he was only brutal within his borders. Yet he was attacked anyway; the US behaved like a revisionist power at a time when it should have been guarding the status quo.</p><p> If the US threat of intervention doesn&#39;t depend on whether or not you send your army outside of your borders — if the US might just attack you anyway because they don&#39;t like you — then the incentive to avoid interstate conflict is reduced. Iraq also weakened US appetite for intervention.</p><p> At the same time, the US was becoming militarily weaker. The War on Terror reoriented the US military toward counterinsurgency and away from defeating enemy armies. The defense-industrial base was allowed to wither — in 1995, the US could produce about <a href="https://twitter.com/matthewstoller/status/1689397134905233408">30 times as many artillery shells</a> as it can now, and China can produce about <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/alarming-navy-intel-slide-warns-of-chinas-200-times-greater-shipbuilding-capacity">200 times as many ships</a> as the US This is a catastrophic loss of hard power, and it means that even a modest diversion of US military resources (like the Ukraine War) can largely remove the threat of US intervention elsewhere.</p><p> Finally, a new great-power coalition arose that was capable of matching or exceeding US power. China&#39;s massive growth has given it a manufacturing capacity as great as the entire West combined, meaning that even if we could fix the problems with our defense-industrial base, we&#39;d be outmatched in a protracted one-on-one fight. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg" width="682" height="491.17691342534505" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:574,&quot;width&quot;:797,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:682,&quot;bytes&quot;:48011,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd3663635-7de7-479e-ade6-830524bf97b0_797x574.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: World Bank</figcaption></figure></div><p> (Also, if you&#39;re tempted to say that the US still spends a lot more than China on its military, please remember that this is not actually true; including off-budget spending, China spends <a href="https://twitter.com/MEaglen/status/1689283338102616065">almost the same amount</a> as the US, and once you take <a href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2023/09/19/china-defense-budget-military-weapons-purchasing-power/">purchasing power differences</a> into account it almost certainly spends more.)</p><p> Real or potential conflict with this New Axis, as I&#39;ve been calling it, now basically absorbs all the military attention of the US and its allies. The Ukraine War is <a href="https://www.worldpoliticsreview.com/russia-war-ukraine-security/">tying down almost all</a> of Europe&#39;s military potential and diverting some US resources as well. The threat of a Chinese invasion of Taiwan is so huge and catastrophic that it will absorb all of the American military attention and resources that aren&#39;t going to Ukraine — and even that may not be enough to win.</p><p> Thus it&#39;s little surprise that the threat of interstate conflict is starting to reemerge in Europe and the surrounding regions. The world is a more ungoverned, lawless place than it was 20 or even 10 years ago. I think Zheng Yongnian of the Chinese University of Hong Kong <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/14/world/asia/china-russia-ukraine.html">put it best last year</a> :</p><blockquote><p> “The old order is swiftly disintegrating, and strongman politics is again ascendant among the world&#39;s great powers,” wrote Mr. Zheng of the Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shenzhen. “Countries are brimming with ambition, like tigers eyeing their prey, keen to find every opportunity among the ruins of the old order.”</p></blockquote><p> Like tigers eyeing their prey. The world is starting to revert into a jungle, where the strong prey upon the weak, and where there is a concomitant requirement that every country build up its own strength; if your neighbor is a tiger, you should probably grow some claws of your own. Old scores that had to wait can now be settled. Disputed bits of territory can now be retaken. Natural resources can now be seized. There are many reasons for countries to fight each other, and now one of the biggest reasons <em>not</em> to fight has been removed.</p><p> (This doesn&#39;t mean I&#39;m predicting a return to the levels of interstate conflict that prevailed before 1945; democratic peace, capitalist peace, low fertility rates, and other factors will still presumably get a say. But <em>one</em> of the major barriers is now gone.)</p><p> Right now Europe, the Middle East, and the Russian periphery are the locus of conflict. But the biggest danger may be in Asia, which is <a href="https://sdsc.bellschool.anu.edu.au/news-events/stories/8489/rising-risk-arms-races-asia-spiralling-major-conflict">engaging</a> in an unprecedented <a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/aerospace-defense/an-intensifying-arms-race-asia-2021-09-21/">arms race</a> . Despite Putin&#39;s aggression, it&#39;s in Asia where the rise of China has disrupted the existing balance of power the most severely. Anyone who is under the illusion that Asia is inherently a more peaceful place than Europe or the Middle East should read some history from before 1980.</p><p> Anyway, Pax Americana always had an expiration date. If the US had avoided the Iraq War and maintained its defense-industrial base, it could have prolonged its hegemony by about a decade, but ultimately the rising power of China would have ensured the return of the multipolarity that existed before World War 2. In any case, it&#39;s over now, and until and unless a new dominant global coalition of nation-states can be forged — either a Chinese-led global order or some kind of expanded democratic hegemony that includes India and large other developing nations — we&#39;re going to have to re-learn how to live in the jungle.</p><p> Over the past two decades it had become fashionable to lambast American hegemony, to speak derisively of “American exceptionalism”, to ridicule America&#39;s self-arrogated function of “world police”, and to yearn for a multipolar world. Well, congratulations, now we have that world. See if you like it better.</p><p> <strong>Update</strong> : <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2023-10-09/israel-hamas-war-us-faces-global-conflict-instability-terrorism?sref=R8NfLgwS">Here is a good article by Hal Brands</a> on the end of Pax Americana, and how it relates to various current conflicts around the world. Here is <a href="https://www.worldpoliticsreview.com/israel-palestinian-conflict-global-security/">a good article by Paul Poast</a> about how the Ukraine war specifically is weakening America&#39;s ability to deter or deescalate conflicts like the one between Hamas and Israel (though I&#39;d argue that our preparation for a war over Taiwan is also a big factor). Both of these authors, unlike me, are experts in the field of international relations. </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/youre-not-going-to-like-what-comes?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/youre-not-going-to-like-what-comes?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>; 
What do Americans want that Biden can give them?Gas prices, immigration, and the economy are things Americans say they care about. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/what-do-americans-want-that-biden https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/what-do-americans-want-that-bidenNoah Smith Fri, 06 Oct 2023 08:56:35 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1038.jpeg" width="1080" height="1038" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0428da6e-10d5-42cf-b0be-2beec46af67e_1080x1